FIG. 1 is a block diagram of a circuit configuration for suppressing disturbances in a bipolar data stream;


FIG. 2 is a schematic of three reference levels such as are used in the circuit configuration according to FIG. 1;


FIG. 3 is a schematic of undersampling of a voltage characteristic in the case of three reference levels corresponding to FIG. 2;


FIG. 4 is a chart showing the behavior of the circuit configuration in accordance with FIG. 1 in the case of the upper level evaluation;


FIG. 5 is a chart showing the behavior of the circuit configuration in accordance with FIG. 1 in the case of the lower level evaluation; and


FIG. 6 shows a schematic of an example of amplitude variation in the data stream with the aid of an eye pattern.
